{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T04:26:55.106Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777264015106_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-010@20260427T001208Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-27\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/queue.py`\n- `tests/test_generation_queue.py`\n- `tests/test_generation_replicate_retry.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation accurately fulfills all acceptance criteria:\n- **Bounded Retry:** Transient failures (exceptions during generation) increment the `attempts` count and requeue the item until `max_attempts` (default 3) is reached.\n- **Terminal Failure:** Validation rejections are correctly treated as terminal failures, transitioning the item to `failed` immediately without further retries.\n- **Error Recording:** The `last_error` column is added to the schema and correctly records the error message from the most recent attempt (transient or terminal).\n- **Concurrency Safety:** The `dequeue` operation remains atomic and correctly increments the `attempts` counter during the claim transaction.\n\n## Completeness\nThe solution is comprehensive:\n- Schema migration handles adding the `last_error` column to existing databases.\n- Both synchronous (`process_one`) and asynchronous (`_worker_loop`) paths are updated.\n- `QueueItem` dataclass and row-mapping logic are updated to include `last_error`.\n- Comprehensive test coverage for terminal-vs-transient failure modes and retry count enforcement.\n\n## Consistency\nThe changes follow existing patterns in the `GenerationQueue` module. The use of SQL `CASE` statements for conditional status updates is consistent with previous state transition logic. Testing patterns match the project's established standards for queue and worker tests.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were introduced. Error recording uses parameterized SQL queries. The `last_error` records exception strings which are safe within the local SQLite context.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is surgical and well-structured. The addition of the `terminal` flag to `mark_failed` provides a clean API for distinguishing between retryable and non-retryable failures. Tests are fast and deterministic.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No blocking issues found. (Note: Full test suite collection fails in the current environment due to unrelated permission issues on `pets.json`, but all relevant generation and queue tests pass.)\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The auto-generated hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were correctly identified as inapplicable to this task as they belong to the daemon startup subsystem, not the generation queue.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-010@20260427t001208z-verify.md"}}
